<TITLE> Sidr deaths relatively low due to forecast, quick response: Health adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  Health adviser ASM Matiur Rahman Tuesday said good forecasting and coastal area inhabitants' rapid response had kept the Sidr death toll relatively low. The environment and property had been unimaginably damaged, he added. The adviser was speaking at a meeting with Dr Alessandro Loretti of the World Health Organisation (WHO). He said the government was working to distribute food, medicine and materials to rebuild homes to cyclone survivors. The adviser thanked the WHO for its assistance. 
